==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cocoanut
<hw>Co"coa*nut`</hw></mhw>
<pr>(k⟦omac⟧"k⟦osl⟧*n⟦ucr⟧t`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>the
edible white meat of a coconut{3}; often shredded for use in e.g. cakes
and curries.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> coconut meat.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>the <er>cocoa palm</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> coconut palm, coco palm, coco, cocoa palm, coconut
tree, Cocos nucifera.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The large, hard-shelled oval nut of the
<prodby>cocoa palm</prodby>. It has a fibrous husk containing a thick
white fibrous meat much used as food, in confections, and in making oil.
It has a central cavity filled (when fresh) with an agreeable milky
liquid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cocobolas</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Cocobolo</ent>⟦br⟧
